`,Ut(t.p,{children:"Tracking longitudinal brain changes from continuous MRI scans is clinically valuable for understanding neurodevelopment and neurodegeneration. However, existing tools require frequent, densely-spaced imaging and cannot forecast what the brain will look like in the future."}),`
